The RAR4 PPMd variant H *model* (unit sub-allocator, suffix-linked context
tree, SEE, decode) was ported from the PPMd var.H codec vendored by
libarchive, which is public-domain:

  archive_ppmd7.c / archive_ppmd7_private.h / archive_ppmd_private.h
  Ppmd7 -- PPMdH codec
  2010-03-12 : Igor Pavlov : Public domain
  Based on PPMd var.H (2001) : Dmitry Shkarin : Public domain

  This code is in the public domain; no copyright notice is required. The
  attribution above is retained as a courtesy and to record provenance.

The solid RAR4 PPMd control flow (each solid file a PPMd block ending with an
escape-code-2 marker; the shared model and escape symbol carried across files;
the RAR range decoder re-initialised per block), the RAR 2.0/2.6 (unpack
v20/v26) LZ decoder (block header, code-length table, and LZ symbol dispatch),
and the RAR3/4 encrypted-header (`-hp`) block framing (plaintext main header,
then per-block `salt[8] · AES-128-CBC(header)` with the cipher re-initialised
per block from the salt-derived IV; the header-CRC wrong-password signal), were
adapted from the BSD Go `rardecode` reader (`archive15.go`, `decrypt_reader.go`,
`decode29.go`, `decode29_ppm.go`, `ppm_model.go`, `decode20.go`,
`decode20_lz.go`, `huffman.go`):

